==English==

===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|exceed||}}
# To be [[larger]], [[greater]] or [[better]] than something else or than expected or desirable.
#:''The company's 2005 revenue '''exceeds''' that of 2004.''
#:''The quality of her essay has '''exceeded''' my expectations.''
# to go [[beyond]] the [[limit]]s of something; to [[surpass]], [[outstrip]] or [[transcend]]
#:''In Super Mario RPG, the name that you are typing in cannot exceed eight characters.''

===Related terms===
* [[excessive]]

===Antonyms===
* to [[fail]]
* to be [[inferior]]

